BBK01.WT5004: Exchange rates on the Frankfurt exchange /PTE 100 = DM ... / Portugal

General: Spot middle rates in Deutsche Mark; difference between buying or selling rate and middle rate in D-Mark: 0.020 up to the end of August 1978 / 0.010 up to the end of 1993 / 0.0030 since 1994. From 29 December 1958 to 30 December 1998 official quotation on the Frankfurt exchange. In accordance with a resolution by the management board of the Frankfurt exchange, with effect from January 1994 the exchange rate of the Escudo was set at four decimal places. For technical reasons, the exchange rates up to December 1993 were extended from three to four decimal places. From 1 January 1999, irrevocable euro conversion rate: Euro 1 = Esc 200.482. Our specific comments refer to "Frankfurt exchange closed on ..." (Devisenbrse am ... geschlossen) or "Quotation suspended on ..." (Notierung am ... ausgesetzt).
